data.description:
Celebrating 500 years of fun in a single day!  The Florida Renaissance Festival is an event the whole family can enjoy—featuring live performances, reenactments, jousting, games, an artisan village, and more!

Held annually since 1991, the festival typically runs between the months of February and March and is open on weekends, from 10 a.m. to sunset, in Quiet Waters Park in Deerfield Beach, FL.

Tickets can be pre-ordered or purchased at the gate.  All major credit cards accepted, and ATMs are available on site.

The Florida Renaissance Festival is produced by the nationally award-winning Bobby Rodriguez Productions, operating in South Florida since 1981.  For more information, visit www.ren-fest.com.
